INSERT INTO `activitycomments` VALUES (1,118,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','',31,'2017-08-02 04:36:28',NULL,NULL,0),(2,118,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear Michele, kindly provide the certification of incorporation (the Foundation should be able to send you a copy), so that we can verify the legal status of the Foundation. (The document you\'ve submitted is just a directory, not the legal document incorporation). thanks!',19,'2017-08-03 05:26:01',NULL,NULL,0),(5,119,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear Carlota, I am trying to conduct the basic legal review of Climate Change Media Ltd., but the following key documents are missing: -Document of incorporation of HMG ONE LIMITED, which was the previous name of Climate Change Media Ltd. (the two documents you attached as documents of incorporation only certify the change of name); -Links to, or copies of, the various current company CSR policies that you have described in your submission. Once you submit these documents we will able to complete the basic legal review!',19,'2017-08-14 12:01:24',NULL,NULL,0),(6,117,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'CooperationAreas','partners','Dear Carlota,\nI have just had a look through this partnership with one of the assessors. I can see that you have not added any Cooperation Areas. This is a mandatory field for the MoU template. If left empty, when you generate he MoU this section will be blank.\nThanking you\nMichelle',1,'2017-08-17 01:37:43',NULL,NULL,0),(8,118,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','According to the  existing  online information (http://tsffoundation.org/), the Schmidt Family Foundation  exists and is stablished in 2006 by its founder , Wendy and Eric Schmidt, The Schmidt Family Foundation works to promote the  sustainable use of energy and natural resources to build resilient systems for food, water, and human resources.\nTheir point of contact is:\n\n•	email: missioninvesting@theschmidt.org; staff@theschmidt.org\n•	mail: 555 Bryant Street, #370, Palo Alto, CA 94301\n•	Phone:650 376 7100\n•	Fax:650 454 8993\n\nThey have been  audited in 2012;2013;2014 and have issued  annual reports for 2012 and 2013 posted on their website.\nThey have teamed up with Ellen MacArthur explains to accelerate the transition towards a circular economy.\nThey focus grantmaking in the areas of Climate and Energy, Ecological Agriculture, and Human Rights. They have funded more than 50 grants some of them in Africa (Haiti, DRC, South Africa and Burundi).\n',NULL,'2017-09-04 07:23:58',NULL,NULL,0),(9,118,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','According to the  existing  online information (http://tsffoundation.org/), the Schmidt Family Foundation  exists and is established in 2006 by its founder , Wendy and Eric Schmidt, The Schmidt Family Foundation works to promote the  sustainable use of energy and natural resources to build resilient systems for food, water, and human resources.\nTheir point of contact is:\n•	email: missioninvesting@theschmidt.org; staff@theschmidt.org\n•	mail: 555 Bryant Street, #370, Palo Alto, CA 94301\n•	Phone:650 376 7100\n•	Fax:650 454 8993\nThey have been  audited in 2012;2013;2014 and have issued  annual reports for 2012 and 2013 posted on their website.\nThey have teamed up with Ellen MacArthur explains to accelerate the transition towards a circular economy.\nThey focus grantmaking in the areas of Climate and Energy, Ecological Agriculture, and Human Rights. They have funded more than 50 grants some of them in Africa (Haiti, DRC, South Africa and Burundi).\n',23,'2017-09-04 07:52:58',NULL,NULL,0),(10,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'','partners','Interested in finding out how to create a Donor Agreement. Does the MoU need to be found, transferred to the new format and then it is possible to sign an agreement? Thank you.',84,'2017-09-08 12:18:51',NULL,NULL,0),(12,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','I am conducting a legal assessment and noticed that following documents you are referring to are not uploaded: Thomson Reuters CRI Report 2016, Environment, Health and Safety Policy and UNGR Business Letter. Can you kindly upload those documents in order for the Legal Office to proceed with the assessment? thank you',106,'2017-10-03 10:47:24',NULL,NULL,0),(13,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','I am conducting legal assessment and noticed that the documents you are referring to are not uploaded in the documents sections. Can you kindly upload the documents so I can proceed with the review? ',106,'2017-10-03 01:36:13',NULL,NULL,0),(14,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Thomson Reuters has the  professionals, technology and human expertise to support UN Environment science- policy agenda.',71,'2017-10-04 04:44:50',NULL,NULL,0),(15,138,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','It is difficult without the direct access to online information portals to answer questions such as \"Risk 5: does the company have any pending legal cases that could jeopardize the position of UN Environment?\" or Risk-06 Does the company work with any Government that is or has been subject to sanctions by the UN Security Council?. It would be helpful to add online information systems where this can be checked. ',96,'2017-10-20 01:57:34',NULL,NULL,0),(16,138,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','In terms of reputational risk, we as UN Environment should realize that without being daring as with whom we\'re partnering we won\'t be able to tackle some of the most defining challenges of the 21st century, such as massively reducing emissions, adapting to a changing climate, ending natural forest loss, etc. Rabobank is one of the most progressive large banks in the world that is willing to make a shift towards sustainable lending. However, we should realize that UN Environment does need to provide proactive support (incl. opening doors to credit guarantors, setting up and/or providing grants to cover some of the non-commercial costs and creating an enabling environment) to put this into practice. In other words, a partnership means both something from the partner we\'re working with (in the case of Rabobank, setting up a USD 1 billion credit facility and start issuing debt according to the criteria agreed) but also from ourselves (i.e. UN Environment delivering on its commitment to help our partner succeed in issuing USD 1 billion in debt for sustainable agricultural production decoupled from deforestation). ',96,'2017-10-20 02:02:51',NULL,NULL,0),(17,139,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','01 - The company doesn’t have a Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) policy however will promote greening of the entertainment business and sustainable operations in the production of the musical show?  \n02- The company doesn’t have any specific environmental policy however will promote greening of the entertainment business.\n',71,'2017-10-23 05:38:22',NULL,NULL,0),(18,135,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','I can confirm that IBM does not work with governments subject to the UN sanction list. In accordance with the IBM website and the answer that we gave on the portal, the Company complies with sanctions issued by the US. Most of the U.S. Treasury Department\'s Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) sanctions are based on United Nations and other International Mandates. The OFAC website has a list of  sanctions programs and which UN Security Council Resolution they relate to. As per the statement from IBM, \"a U.S. company like IBM is prohibited from any trade of goods and services that originated from or passed through any entity\" in the sanctioned countries. Therefore, you are correct in that the answer to assessment question point 5 regarding sanctions should be NO, not YES. ',125,'2017-11-13 06:21:24',NULL,NULL,0),(19,135,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','I can confirm that IBM does not work with governments subject to the UN sanction list. In accordance with the IBM website and the answer that we gave on the portal, the Company complies with sanctions issued by the US. Most of the U.S. Treasury Department\'s Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) sanctions are based on United Nations and other International Mandates. The OFAC website has a list of  sanctions programs and which UN Security Council Resolution they relate to. As per the statement from IBM, \"a U.S. company like IBM is prohibited from any trade of goods and services that originated from or passed through any entity\" in the sanctioned countries. Therefore, you are correct in that the answer to assessment question point 5 regarding sanctions should be NO, not YES. ',125,'2017-11-13 06:21:29',NULL,NULL,0),(20,135,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Please clarify the assessment on point 5 above (the first Basic Risk Assessment. According to the comments the reply should be NO, rather than YES (or some additional information provided under the notes)',47,'2017-11-08 03:50:57',NULL,NULL,0),(21,135,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','For clarification: IBM requested to make alterations to the MoU that is generated from the portal. These changes have been cleared by the legal unit. Therefore, the MoU, inclusive of the changes agreed upon by legal and IBM, is the version that is uploaded and signed onto the portal',80,'2017-11-15 06:26:59',NULL,NULL,0),(22,149,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','@Adima Nyodero, dear Adima, I was trying to upload their annual report, but it seems the document is too big to be uploaded, is there a way we can solve this problem? And the same document \"in the news\" was uploaded twice due to delayed reaction, is it possible to delete the extra one? Thank you!',11,'2017-12-04 01:17:28',NULL,NULL,0),(23,150,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','The answer to the first question about publishing an environmental/sustainability report does not appear here for some reason. The answer is \"yes\" and I have attached it as a separate document with the other attachments.',172,'2018-01-11 06:49:47',NULL,NULL,0),(24,164,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Please note that you have created the profile for a service. The name of the parent company is One 97 Communications Private Limited. ',32,'2018-02-12 03:01:53',NULL,NULL,0),(25,176,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'CooperationAreas','partners','Cooperation Areas:\nTo improve livelihoods of current and future generations of rice growers and other value chain actors.\nTo meet consumer needs for food security, food safety and quality of rice and rice products.\nTo manage natural resources efficiently throughout the value chain.\nTo protect the natural environment from disruptive effects of rice production and processing.\nTo prevent adverse impacts on neighboring communities and contribute to their development.\nTo adapt rice production systems to changing climates and mitigate greenhouse gas emissions throughout the value chain.\nTo respect labour rights and promote the well-being of workers.\nTo conduct business with integrity and transparency.',158,'2018-02-27 10:31:24',NULL,NULL,0),(26,68,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Freshwater Unit has reviewed the due diligence reports. The findings of the reports and the risks associated with UN Environment partnering with Google do not relate to the technical support that Google intends to provide to UN Environment in the form of data and analysis that supports SDG 6. Rather, the findings of these reports should to be considered and where appropriate mitigated for at the division and corporate level. ',2083,'2018-03-13 02:37:28',NULL,NULL,0),(27,177,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Endorse',NULL,'2018-03-23 10:35:14',NULL,NULL,0),(32,505,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear All,\n\nThis is to inform you on the status of the partnership with World Sailing.\n\nThere has been confusion on whether World Sailing was a for