',2079,'2019-06-04 08:50:09',NULL,NULL,0),(1173,1168,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'DueDiligence','partners','Nature Kenya has provided the required documentation and their status as a not-for-profit entity has been cleared by our Legal Unit. In terms of the track record of Nature Kenya, we have shared the feedback received from partners in terms of their performance. This refers not only in the context of our own experience during the project preparation phase for the last two years that was successfully completed but also other partners within and outside our organization. I refer to the text provided again for ease of reference: Nature Kenya successfully contributed to the WCMC GEF Biodiversity Indicators Partnership (BIP) project representing views from Africa in the development of Biodiversity Indicators. UNEP-WCMC reports to have enjoyed a long and successful relationship with Nature Kenya. Since the establishment of the BIP in 2017, Nature Kenya played a key role in supporting the development and strategic direction of the Partnership, serving on the BIP Steering Committee, and ensuring that the Partnership was relevant to and addressed the national indicator needs of Parties to the CBD. Nature Kenya has also supported Birdlife International in the development of global indicators brought together under the BIP.  Other GEF experience includes the most recent project with UNDP completed in 2015 (full size project - US$ 5 million). Nature Kenya has served in the Birdlife International Global Council and has generated knowledge products that have been taken up globally. Nature Kenya is the pioneer of the KBAs Concept that was launched in Hawaii by 11 partners including Birdlife International who represent Nature Kenya in the partnership. As IUCN member, Nature Kenya serves in several IUCN commissions and is a member of the Kenya IUCN Committee. ',2648,'2019-06-04 12:48:34',NULL,NULL,0),(1174,1478,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear Henry, over to you for valid