low the answer to each question/comment: \n\nAnswer 1)  The Technical University of Denmark is a government-financed university. Hence, we selected the category, university (government) organization, as opposed to a non-profit making organization in the Partners portal.  Before I started to develop the agreement, I also had to make a new partner submission for validation in the Partners Portal. This is where we categorized DTU as university (government) organization.  Kindly see the validation email attached at the bottom of my email.  Therefore, we retain the clause as it is. \n\nAnswer 2)  The due dates have been harmonized in both documents: Activity 1. 30 Nov 2019; Activity 2. 23 September 2019; and Activity 3. 30 November 2019. \n\nAnswer 3)  It has been updated to reflect 23 Sept 2019 as the due date. \n\nAnswer 4)  Expected results have been added as requested.  \n\nAnswer 5)  Regarding Clause 4, in the Partners Portal, we need to specify an exact date because it does not allow me to write “upon signature of both parties”.  I indicated 19 August, thinking that it would not take long to process this.  Anyhow, now I have amended the date to be 1 September 2019.  I hope that the process would be completed by then. \n\nAs for the end date of the agreement, 31 December 2021 is the correct end date. We intend to have this SSFA as a multiyear agreement that will also include future EGR and AGR work.  As you may be aware, we work with DTU to produce EGR and AGR on a yearly basis.  We will certainly continue to work with them in foreseeable future.  When we have additional funding (which is expected) coming in, we will amend the agreement to include Activity 4, 5, … accordingly. Please also note that the PIMS Project ID 02041 where the EGR and AGR work is housed (and this Agreement is linked to) lasts until 31 December 2023.  So, the end date of this agreement being 31 December 2021 is within the end date of the project. Before submitting the agreement for your review, we already consulted with Nada and Tito whether there is any restriction in having an agreement for such a period of time, and they confirmed that as long as it is well within the project duration, it is acceptable. \n\nRegarding Clause 14, perhaps you are not aware that the standard clause has been changed by CSS in the portal.  This clause used to state the period of the entire agreement, but now it gives you the flexibility of indicating how many more months after the specified end date in clause 4.…\"..and shall remain valid for a period of 6 months, after the end date specified in clause 4 unless terminated earlier pursuant to clause 11 above.\"  I consulted with CSS and they said the default value (of months) is between 1 to 12 months. We discussed with DTU and decided to go with 6 months.  As a result, this agreement would remain valid for a period of 6 months after 31 December 2021. \n\nAnswer 6) Wire instructions updated to include:  IBAN: DK2430004183089927  and  SWIFT: DABADKKKXXX\n\nAnswer 7)  In Clause 7, we indicated that the date of substantive and financial reporting is 31 March 2020 for Activity 1, 2 and 3.  It should give DTU enough time to complete the reporting. \n',630,'2019-08-19 15:29:57',NULL,NULL,0),(1464,771,1692,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please correct the dates and referred wording as per my email. Thank you.',817,'2019-08-19 15:39:52',NULL,NULL,0),(1465,439,1642,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Thanks Florence, I made the changes. As I couldn\'t edit everything some things to be deleted are in brackets now like in a resolution. To be cleaned up later in Word.\nRegarding some of your comments:\n5) We need to end it a bit earlier as we need to get the funds out in 2019.\n6) UCC also in earlier agreements didn\'t have a signatory. It\'s a bank account.',1961,'2019-08-19 16:13:16',NULL,NULL,0),(1466,1547,1329,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','.',2042,'2019-08-20 09:20:55',NULL,NULL,0),(1467,445,987,511,N