ality Assurance)',2112,'2019-08-20 11:04:43',NULL,NULL,0),(1470,194,1800,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','I have reviewed the legal instrument and below are my comments. Please address them and resubmit for my review:\n1)	In 1st Paragraph – last sentence…” an international organization for “ please include the following before the brackets (details attached)\n“for establishing international standards for environmental policy and provide direction to international initiatives based on scientific knowledge”\n\n2)	Under Article I. The Contribution – No. 1 Kindly update the font and spacing for the banking details.\n\n3)	Under Article VIII. Advertisement of the Contribution – No. 1 Kindly remove the brackets in the last sentence…..”by UNEP of [the Donor], its products or services”\n\n4)	Under Article XIV – 1st paragraph, in place of upon September 2019, kindly use ‘upon signature by both parties’ Also note that you have stated the agreement will remain effective for 56 months until 1st June 2020 – kindly clarify since the months from now to June 1st 2020 does not tally to 56 months.\n\nThank you.\n (Quality Assurance)',2112,'2019-08-20 12:18:52',NULL,NULL,0),(1471,1928,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','Hi Adamou. I will need more information on this organization before I could consider it for validation. Is the name an acronym of some sorts?',592,'2019-08-20 12:23:18',NULL,NULL,0),(1472,878,1584,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Clause 4. See previous comment. Activities only funded from EF funds until 31 Dec 2019 - not activities can be funded/authorised beyond this date. Please review end date of this agreement.',2519,'2019-08-20 15:31:43',NULL,NULL,0),(1473,1741,1822,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please refer to email for request amendment on clause 23 - Email dated 20.08.2019',2520,'2019-08-20 16:12:08',NULL,NULL,0),(1474,344,1614,512,NULL,2,'Amendments','agreements','Monika please review and approve this no-cost amendment to the SSFA with Charles Darwin Foundation - legal agreement expires end of this month so this is urgent.',610,'2019-08-21 11:05:43',NULL,NULL,0),(1475,445,516,509,NULL,2,'Amendments','agreements','Monika kindly review/approve this amendment to a SSFA with GRID-Arendal. Thank you.',610,'2019-08-21 11:07:19',NULL,NULL,0),(1476,1732,1652,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Concerning the duration of the SSFA, we have given due consideration on your comments and we would like to propose a compromised solution by having the SSFA last until 31 December 2020 instead of 31 Dec 2021.  Here are the reasons why this is important and urgent:\n\n1.	The revised end-date will allow us to continue to engage DTU over the next-year’s EGR and AGR reports.  They will need to be delivered by 30 November 2020, prior to the UNFCCC Climate COP, as it has always been.  We cannot have a shorter duration for this SSFA, than that end-date (Dec. 2020), because it needs to fit the production cycles of both these reports. \n2.	As far as we know, per the existing guidance there is no clear restriction on the duration of a SSFA.  We understand your point about a potential concern when an audit is carried out; however, we would need to receive from you any relevant documents that talk about audit query related to an agreement longer than one year, to convince us of your point. If there is no such guidance, then we really need to go for an SSFA that runs until the end of December 2020 to allow for coherent and consistent, successful delivery of these key reports, one of which is a flagship knowledge product recognized as such by our new ED.  \n',630,'2019-08-21 14:01:41',NULL,NULL,0),(1477,1762,1766,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','The changes proposed to the draft PCA appear to be related to reporting obligations only which should be reviewed and cleared by the concerned PO and FMO/AO. It is unclear why the draft PCA has triggered legal review. Concerned FMO/AO to confirm (by e-m