s clause derives from UNEP’s status as a UN entity, it cannot be made reciprocal to Partners either. Just to clarify further, the indemnity clause does not mean that UNEP’s partner shall take all the responsibility or represent UNEP in court --- UNEP cannot be taken to court as it is immune from jurisdiction. The clause only entails that in case there were third parties raising claims against UNEP, UNEP would communicate such claim to the Partner and the Partner would be responsible for conveying the information about UNEP’s immunity from jurisdiction, to the court where actions may have been instituted. Immunity from jurisdiction is part of the immunities recognized to the UN in the 1946 Convention on the Privileges and Immunities of the UN. Hope that helps, please let us know if the Partner continues to push back and we can explore further. All the best, Neda. ',2679,'2019-09-12 13:00:42',NULL,NULL,0),(1645,1831,1953,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','select Frank Turyatunga  as the approving officer.',1958,'2019-09-12 17:20:50',NULL,NULL,0),(1646,1817,1889,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','please update the workflow',1958,'2019-09-12 17:39:51',NULL,NULL,0),(1647,1854,1929,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Add quality control, change certifying to Nancy, recommender to JIm and approver as Elizabeth if above $100k',1958,'2019-09-13 08:46:36',NULL,NULL,0),(1648,1854,1927,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Add quality control, change certifying to Nancy, recommender to JIm and approver as Elizabeth if above $100k',1958,'2019-09-13 08:47:55',NULL,NULL,0),(1649,1854,1928,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Add quality control, change certifying to Nancy, recommender to JIm and approver as Elizabeth if above $100k',1958,'2019-09-13 08:48:56',NULL,NULL,0),(1650,1841,1895,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Add quality control, change certifying to Nancy, recommender to JIm and approver as Elizabeth if above $100