ry','agreements','Please change UNEP Signatory name & title',2082,'2019-11-01 09:46:08',NULL,NULL,0),(1932,1736,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear Shelly and Francis, \n\nThank you for looping me in. As per Shelly’s advice, the intended partner is ‘Global Water Partnership – Mediterranean’ (GWP-Med). GWP-Med, as per its website ‘is the Mediterranean Regional Water Partnership of the inter-governmental organisation Global Water Partnership (GWP).’ The GWP-Med Secretariat, again as per its website is ‘hosted by the Mediterranean Information Office for Environment, Culture and Sustainable Development (MIO-ECSDE), which legally represents GWP-Med (based on a Host Institute Agreement between the Global Water Partnership Organisation and MIO-ECSDE).’ I have reviewed the Host Institute Agreement which has been uploaded to the portal and note that while the Global Water Partnership Organisation has its own legal personality, established in Sweden, its Regional Water Partnerships (of which GWP-Med is one) ‘are attached to host institutions [in this case MIO-ECSDE] that administer funds and employ staff on their behalf’. Further, at page 1 it states ‘GWP Mediterranean Regional Water Partnership … is an independent organisation, but it does not have legal personality…’\n\nGiven the above, we advise that the partner should be registered in the portal as ‘Mediterranean Information Office for Environment, Culture and Sustainable Development (MIO-ECSDE)’. \n\nMany thanks\nNeda \n',2679,'2019-11-01 09:50:09',NULL,NULL,0),(1933,2029,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Dear Sirinart and Francis, \n\nThank you for looping me in. Based on the document provided – which seems to be the constitution of the entity – we would advise registering this partner as not-for-profit. The basis for this advice is that:\n•	As per s67(1) of its constitution, ‘The income and property of the company must be applied solely towards the promotion of the objects of the company and no portion of the income and property may be paid or transferred directly or indirectly by way of dividend, bonus or otherwise by way of profit to the members of the company.’\n•	Further, according to its constitution, it is a company limited by guarantee, which as you point out, in Singapore is usually formed for not-for-profit purposes. Please also see guidance to this effect from the Singapore Accounting and Corporate Regulatory Authority, a government agency: https://www.acra.gov.sg/how-to-guides/setting-up-a-local-company/determining-the-company-type. \n\nWe note however that it does not seem that the certificate of incorporation for the entity has been provided, and that the document uploaded is just the company’s constitution. We advise that the certificate of incorporation is also provided. Kindly advise if we have misunderstood this. \n\nMany thanks\nNeda \n\n',2679,'2019-11-01 09:53:40',NULL,NULL,0),(1934,436,2067,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Pls amend the amount to $85k and resubmit',55,'2019-11-01 09:57:05',NULL,NULL,0),(1935,2030,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Due diligence assessed and approved',51,'2019-11-01 12:30:10',NULL,NULL,0),(1936,753,2297,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Dear Vanda,\nThe attached UN-UN Agreement was generated by FAO and following exchanges and discussions, was signed in October 2019 by FAO (on behalf of the South West Indian Ocean Fisheries Commission - SWIOFC) and UNEP (on behalf of the Nairobi Convention).  The signed UN-UN contribution agreement  is attached including a summary of outputs, logical framework and work plan.',520,'2019-11-01 17:11:38',NULL,NULL,0),(1937,1332,2312,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','A per the request by the Programme Officer',577,'2019-11-01 18:42:31',NULL,NULL,0),(1938,1628,1879,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Sinikinesh, as discussed, please confirm that the leasing of boat for the expedition will be done in accordance to the proc