ttps://asia.nikkei.com/Companies/Mitsui-Chemicals-Inc |  https://apps1.unep.org/partners/uploads/mitsui_chemicals_report_2018_1571897530.pdf   (pg. 120)), as well as a shareholder of a number of Mitusi Chemical subsidiary companies (https://www.mitsuichem.com/en/corporate/group/oversea_05.htm). \n\nPlease also see the document attached in the portal documents section to know more about Mitsui Chemicals\' shareholders, and their potential links to weapons/the weapons industry.',2095,'2019-12-10 10:38:23',NULL,NULL,0),(2109,2045,2446,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Budget redeploy has been processed. Thank you',2116,'2019-12-10 11:48:09',NULL,NULL,0),(2110,1797,2196,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please review comments as per email ',108,'2019-12-10 13:32:20',NULL,NULL,0),(2111,1013,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','These are a few brief notes on the topic of the working relationship with OGCI as of December 2019.\n \nUNEP and OGCI have been working directly as part of the Methane Science Studies, in addition to other points of contact detailed in the due diligence. Some of the OGCI companies (BP, Equinor, Eni, Repsol, Shell, Total) are also part to another multi-stakeholder initiative implemented by the Energy and Climate Branch: the Oil and Gas Methane Partnership. This due diligence process is in relation to the Methane Science Studies, and the original donor agreement and the governing framework for the Methane Science Studies are attached as support documents. To date, OGCI has donated $6M to UNEP for the Methane Science Studies. More details on the Methane Science Studies workstream and individual studies are included in the attached CCAC Methane Science Studies brief. The original partnership and donations were approved by the executive director at the time (please see attached MoUs_CCAC_Methane Studies_Partnership clearance). We are currently seeking approval to update the donor agreement to accept an additional $885,000 from OGCI.\n \nThe companies of OGCI have numerous responsibilities towards the Methane Science Studies, which are detailed in the Methane Science Studies Framework and Donor Agreement, both of which are attached. First, in the context of the Methane Science Studies, the payments have been made in a timely fashion. Secondly, the framework of the Methane Science Studies lists a number of obligations with respect to the OGCI companies with respect to: attending and contributing to Steering Committee meetings, attending and contributing to Technical Working Group meetings, facilitating permissions and conversations with government representatives, sharing data, and generally ensuring that the studies are grounded in an understanding of how oil and gas systems operate.\n \nIn the working relationship to date, there have been no reputational impacts to UNEP through our collaboration with OGCI companies. The UNEP staff which participate in the Methane Science Studies, as well as staff which participate in other collaborative projects with OGCI, regularly attend international meetings and conferences to present on the topic of methane. There has been no evidence of reputational damage at these conferences. Additionally, internet searching reveals no articles or other results that state that the Methane Science Studies or the Oil and Gas Methane Partnership are greenwashing.\n',2289,'2019-12-10 21:53:43',NULL,NULL,0),(2112,445,987,754,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements',', please check that the funds related to NW18 in this SSFA have been offset. Many thanks,\n',2042,'2019-12-11 11:05:25',NULL,NULL,0),(2113,450,2477,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Change Article 2 to 1 Month\nChange Article 14 to 1 Month\nMatch outputs on SSFA with those in Annex 1 or vice versa',2082,'2019-12-11 13:54:47',NULL,NULL,0),(2114,1586,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','@nkwenti\nThey are engaged through an SSFA - is that the question?',320,'2019-12-11 18:10:05',NULL,NULL,0),(21