P intends to have with the partner? the dossier states that \"By partnering with UN Environment, La Banque Agricole will increase its capacity to manage climate risks and support is client base in building climate resilience. This will in turn help UNEP deliver its programme of work and increase its influence in the region.\" what are the benefits of this to UNEP and how will these activities/collaboration contribute towards UNEP;s POW? ',2125,'2020-04-02 19:06:01',NULL,NULL,0),(2533,2174,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','@Camila Nkwenti Regarding your comment: \"Please could the submitting office provide more information regarding the collaboration hat UNEP intends to have with the partner? the dossier states that \"By partnering with UN Environment, La Banque Agricole will increase its capacity to manage climate risks and support is client base in building climate resilience. This will in turn help UNEP deliver its programme of work and increase its influence in the region.\" what are the benefits of this to UNEP and how will these activities/collaboration contribute towards UNEP;s POW?\"\n\nPlease note that the Microfinance for Ecosystem-based Adaptation (MEbA) project (www.unepmeba.org) aims at increasing capacities in partner financial institutions to deliver EbA-oriented micro-loans and improve the management of risks and information in agricultural lending to increase investment towards sustainable adaptation approaches. The intention is to sign an MoU that will allow the project to deliver technical assistance to La Banque Agricole, through executing partners, in order to increase such capacity. In the end it is expected that La Banque Agricole will be able to promote EbA activities among small scale farmers in Senegal. This contributes UNEP\'s PoW in the Climate Change subprograme EA.1. (a) Countries increasingly advance their national adaptation plans which integrate ecosystem-based adaptation and the following indicators: (ii) The number of countries supported by UNEP that have technical capacity to integrate ecosystem-based management into national adaptation plans and (iii) The number of countries supported by UNEP that are ready to access or have accessed climate change adaptation finance to implement adaptation plans.\nIt should be noted that La Banque Agricole is in stage 2 of its accreditation process to the GCF and will therefore play a significant role in Senegal\'s country strategy to access adaptation finance.\n',2236,'2020-04-02 19:19:37',NULL,NULL,0),(2534,2174,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'DueDiligence','partners','Regarding your comment: \"Please could the submitting office provide more information regarding the collaboration hat UNEP intends to have with the partner? the dossier states that \"By partnering with UN Environment, La Banque Agricole will increase its capacity to manage climate risks and support is client base in building climate resilience. This will in turn help UNEP deliver its programme of work and increase its influence in the region.\" what are the benefits of this to UNEP and how will these activities/collaboration contribute towards UNEP;s POW?\"\nPlease note that the Microfinance for Ecosystem-based Adaptation (MEbA) project (www.unepmeba.org) aims at increasing capacities in partner financial institutions to deliver EbA-oriented micro-loans and improve the management of risks and information in agricultural lending to increase investment towards sustainable adaptation approaches. The intention is to sign an MoU that will allow the project to deliver technical assistance to La Banque Agricole, through executing partners, in order to increase such capacity. In the end it is expected that La Banque Agricole will be able to promote EbA activities among small scale farmers in Senegal. This contributes UNEP\'s PoW in the Climate Change subprograme EA.1. (a) Countries increasingly advance their national adaptation plans which integrate ecosystem-based adaptation and the following indicators: 