58,2529,3344,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','1.	Please provide Annexes A and B as mentioned in the introduction of the Agreement.\n2.	Please provide Annex I under Article III relating to the Activity implementation and Budget overview, please ensure that the budget breakdown includes 1%Levy of $9,408, and 13% of 109,311.\n3.	Kindly add in the Article V the following as point 2:\nPursuant to paragraph 10(a) of United Nations General Assembly Resolution 72/279 of 31 May 2018, the Donor agrees that an amount corresponding to 1% of the contribution to innovative activities shall be paid to fund the United Nations Resident Coordinator System. This amount, hereinafter referred to as the “coordination levy” will be held in trust by UNEP until transfer to the United Nations Secretariat for deposit into the United Nations Special Purpose Trust Fund for the reinvigorated Resident Coordinator system, which has been established to fund the UN Resident Coordinator System and is managed by the United Nations Secretariat. \n\nThe Donor acknowledges that once the coordination levy has been transferred by UNEP to the United Nations Secretariat, UNEP is not responsible for the use of the coordination levy and does not assume any liability. The fiduciary responsibility lies with the United Nations Secretariat as the manager of the Resident Coordinator system. \n\nThe coordination levy does not form part of UNEP’s cost recovery and is additional to the costs of UNEP to implement the activity or activities covered by the contribution. Accordingly, there is no normal obligation for UNEP to refund the levy, in part or in full, even where the activities covered by the contribution are not carried out in full by UNEP. As deemed necessary by the donor- and especially where the scale of the resources concerned or reputational risk justify the refund transaction costs – the donor can submit a request for refund to the United nations Secretariat directly or through the United Nations entity. The responsibility to refund the levy lies with the United Nations Secretariat, and not with the concerned entity of the United Nations. \n\nThe coordination levy for this agreement is $9,408. The amounts indicated on the payment schedule, refer to article I, includes the appropriate portion of the disbursements of the coordination levy and the payments of the contribution.\nThank you.\n',2042,'2020-10-12 13:17:49',NULL,NULL,0),(3159,2359,3307,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','SSFA for your quality assurance approval',1251,'2020-10-12 15:37:10',NULL,NULL,0),(3160,2562,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Documents','partners','Dear Isabel/Camila, requesting your assistance to ascertain the Legal/Partner type of this organization.',28,'2020-10-12 15:37:59',NULL,NULL,0),(3161,374,3347,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','The budget table for work package 4 is not accurate. You will receive from me a track change version with modifications included. Please check again the figures of work package 3 as well. Thank you. (Quality Assurance)',76,'2020-10-12 15:47:02',NULL,NULL,0),(3162,374,3347,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','I have revised both work packages budget and deleted decimals, both sub-totals are now accurate. ',447,'2020-10-12 16:14:06',NULL,NULL,0),(3163,374,3347,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','The total which now amounts to 44,234 USD, has not been amended accordingly. It will also need to be amended in the text of the SSFA itself. (Quality Assurance)',76,'2020-10-12 16:23:34',NULL,NULL,0),(3164,391,3325,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Thanks for the explanation Helena.   This addresses my concerns.   ',1194,'2020-10-12 17:10:51',NULL,NULL,0),(3165,872,3354,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Thanks Florence. The draft is modified accordingly and resubmitted for your kind review.',2297,'2020-10-12 18:01:50',NULL,NULL,0),(3166,2529,3344,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Comment Item No. 3 done as requested.