P’s role in monitoring the media and the implementation of the partnership itself to cater for the reputational risk.\n\n2.	We therefore suggest the following: \na.	More detailed information regarding the contribution of the partnerships to the PoW and SDGs. \nb.	Past concrete achievements. What will the focus of this renewed collaboration be (some information is on the risk mitigation plan but good be good to add it to the dd).\nc.	As to the risk mitigation plan:\n\n-	Provide concrete examples that speak to this statement “…Moreover, the refiners based in Switzerland, such as Argor, are involved in the Government-Sponsored Swiss Better Gold Initiative through which a portion of their gold is used to develop social and environmental programmes in the countries of origin.”\nd.	Clarify UNEP’s role in terms of monitoring risks, in particularly, potential reputational risks.\n\n\n',2125,'2021-02-12 17:47:27',NULL,NULL,0),(3640,1944,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Kindly advise as to the nature of the engagement of the partner and how the engagement will contribute towards UNEP\'s work.',2125,'2021-02-12 17:56:45',NULL,NULL,0),(3641,445,3619,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Submitting SSFA with GRID - Arendal for review',463,'2021-02-14 15:47:59',NULL,NULL,0),(3642,1482,3776,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements',' (Quality Assurance)',2161,'2021-02-15 14:34:47',NULL,NULL,0),(3643,1944,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','Akvo will support UNEP through the SSFA to meet several requests in UNEA resolutions which are incorporated into the PoW of UNEP - going forward the focus is on the development of a digital platform in response to UNEA 4/6 para 3 building on existing initiatives, the Global Partnership on Marine Litter (UNEP was requested to strengthen its input to the GPML in resolution 3/7 para 7). This digital platform will make it possible to consolidate and integrate multiple sources of data and information on marine litter and plastic pollution prevention to guide action, increase coordination and connect stakeholders. This is a key aspect in an arena where more and more actors are engaging with little or no coordination. To that effect, matchmaking functionalities are being developed to support coordination. The platform will feed in information to the World Environment Situation Room and consultations are ongoing with partners and usergroups to ensure that it is meeting the needs of the users in relation to this issue - this work sits in PoW 522.4. ',320,'2021-02-15 17:14:41',NULL,NULL,0),(3644,445,3619,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','I have reviewed the legal instruments and below are my comments. Kindly address them and resubmit.\n1.	In the Preamble: 1. Project/Programme objectives to which the small-scale funding contributes which reads in part, “This project will contribute to UNEP of Work Subprogramme..” kindly have it read “This project will contribute to UNEP Subprogramme of Work”\n2.	Aims:  This section has been left blank however the paragraphs above it have both the objectives and aim of the SSFA.  Kindly split the two and have the Aim move to its section.\nThank you. \n (Quality Assurance)',2112,'2021-02-15 17:59:44',NULL,NULL,0),(3645,2521,3669,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','This is a non standard agreement which does not subject to portal approval. You will simply need to upload the signed agreement once signed',2082,'2021-02-16 05:44:49',NULL,NULL,0),(3646,2672,3879,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please see my email comments',2082,'2021-02-16 06:05:47',NULL,NULL,0),(3647,1482,3776,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please revise as per email',2082,'2021-02-16 06:45:12',NULL,NULL,0),(3648,445,3619,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','All comments addressed and the agreement resubmitted',463,'2021-02-16 14:44:05',NULL,NULL,0),(3649,2750,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Please upload a translated version of th