ng RIO+20, South African and Brazilian World Cups and Brazilian Olympic Games, engaging in total resources around USD 10 M in project activities. We are also discussing with Airbnb and International Olympic Committee a campaign for Tokyo 2021. However, outside the scope of large events, UNEP’s tourism programme has limited funds to implement the Campaign and to promote demand for sustainable tourism products and services. In this sense, UNEP partners with tourism destinations, NGO’s and private sector partners that are willing to finance their own implementation of the Green Passport campaign aligned to our advice and criteria. By signing this agreement this organisation can align their tourism strategic planning with financial mechanisms to support the implementation of these campaigns, and align with the French recovery plans on tourism, and we can ensure sustainable tourism actions are included in their regional policies. The  Comité Départemental du Tourisme de l’Anjou  will engage in the Campaign the private sector and local communities in order to implement a model of sustainable tourism that would support economic growth and insure protection of cultural and natural heritage of the Region. UNEP will also take advantage of this engagement to bring private sectors in the region to support voluntary initiatives to mainstream SCP and combat pollution such as the global tourism plastics initiative. Considering the governmental status of the region, a due diligence is not required. As the online portal agreements do not cater for French versions, it was suggested to upload a pdf version of the word document once MOU is signed. The end date of the signature is 31-12-2025. ',447,'2021-04-01 22:53:34',NULL,NULL,0),(3814,2598,4026,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please insert full address. Please modify start event date to 5th or 6th April. Thanks.',1139,'2021-04-02 11:24:20',NULL,NULL,0),(3815,53,3987,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please ch