to my email',2082,'2021-08-20 06:07:58',NULL,NULL,0),(4317,2907,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Thank you for your feedback. With regard to your first question, on September 7 2021 the Court of Cassation will rule on the appeals filed against the indictments for financing terrorism, endangering peoples’ lives and violating an embargo. https://bit.ly/2W8a6Wu It will also consider an appeal by rights groups and former employees to uphold the charge of complicity in crimes against humanity. https://bit.ly/2ViVRNP With regard to the second question, Holcim AG conducts extractive activities related to cement production, including mining of limestone. The Company services the oil and gas sector with products including well cement solutions. https://bit.ly/3AXLTRH ',3197,'2021-08-20 11:42:58',NULL,NULL,0),(4318,450,4492,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please see email for comments. Thank you Clare (Quality Assurance)',215,'2021-08-20 13:38:53',NULL,NULL,0),(4319,2907,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Our objection is based on the elements raised in our first comment:\n1) With regard to the lawsuit pending before the French courts, the due diligence questionnaire indicates in various questions that “Charges re: supporting armed groups in Syria have been lifted”. However, the information provided in answer to our comment reveals that the status of the lawsuit is as follows. On 7 November 2019, the Paris Court of Appeals upheld the indictment of the company for deliberate endangerment of people’s lives, financing of terrorism and violation of an embargo. However, the court overturned the indictment for complicity in crimes against humanity committed in Syria – notably by the Islamic State. Both aspects of the appeal decision have been contested before the Cour of Cassation (the highest/supreme French judicial court). So, the Cour de Cassation will rule on whether the charges of endangerment of people’s lives, financing of terrorism and violation of an embargo should remain, and whether the charges of complicity in crimes against humanity committed in Syria should be reinstated. \nThe charges are therefore maintained at the moment and if the Cour de Cassation confirms them, Holcim AG will be prosecuted for endangerment of people’s lives, financing of terrorism and violation of an embargo (or one or two of these, and maybe with complicity of crimes against humanity added to the list). \n\nWe are not certain that the monitoring mechanism put in place to follow the development of this case is sufficient to address the risks posed by Holcim AG as these charges are extremely serious. \n\nFurthermore, although ensuring that Holcim AG does not use UNEP’s name or logo in any communication related to its activities in Syria and in Myanmar or does not develop communication that would be detrimental to UNEP is of course necessary, this does not address the question of the risks posed by the critics or claims that could be laid against UNEP by the civil parties to the lawsuit or any other organisation working on behalf of the environment or the victims of the Syrian conflict.\n\n2) With regard to the question of extractive activities, although there is indeed value in engaging with the cement and building sector to promote sustainable buildings and building processes, the fact that Holcim AG is involved in the oil and gas industry through supplying well and drilling solutions, namely via providing cement for the wells raises additional questions. \n\nFor these reasons, we would recommend discussion this partner collectively and refer the decision to the Chair of the Partnership Committee. ',3039,'2021-08-20 15:38:20',NULL,NULL,0),(4320,2143,4520,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Please as an amendment not an original agreement',1958,'2021-08-23 09:33:32',NULL,NULL,0),(4321,911,4493,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Returned for amendment.',2360,'2021-08-23 12:32:44',NULL,NULL,0),(4