FA cannot be extended until June 2022. Please adjust all dates in the SSFA narrative and annexes to reflect no later than 31-Dec-2021. (2) The references to end dates are not consistent throughout the document : para 3 indicates a timeframe of 1-Jul-2021-30-Jun-2022, but para 7 indicates final financial statement is due on 31-Dec-2021, and Annex I Implementation timeframe is through end of 2021. Please adjust so that all end dates are the same (3) In the header on page 1, the inventory number BAH/PHN/84/TAS/36 has a typo - it should be \"PHA\" noy \"PHN.\" (4) Para 4 indicates a start date of 1 July 2021. Please change the date to a realistic start date.',327,'2021-09-19 09:26:37',NULL,NULL,0),(4467,2334,4437,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','After reviewing the draft SSFA from the legal standpoint: \nUnder Clause 12, we note that our standard Dispute Settlement provision that provides alternate dispute settlement mechanism has been revised. While there is a reference to settle disputes in a good faith, there should be also a reference to arbitration and its rules and procedures.  In this regard please note that Article VIII, Section 29 of the Convention on the Privileges and Immunities of the United Nations provides that, “the United Nations shall make provisions for appropriate modes of settlement of: (a) disputes arising out of contracts or other disputes of a private law character to which the United Nations is a party; (b) disputes involving any official of the United Nations who by reason of his official position enjoys immunity, if immunity has not been waived by the Secretary-General.” ',3165,'2021-09-20 11:03:35',NULL,NULL,0),(4468,2334,4437,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','This provision is the basis for the arbitration and dispute resolution clauses set forth in all United Nations (and UNEP) contracts. Although the United Nations does not agree to waive its privileges and immunities in its contracts, by agreeing to arbitrate disputes of a private law character as a full and final resolution thereof, such as disputes arising out of contracts, the United Nations is providing for an “appropriate mode of settlement” of such dispute. Thus, such a dispute resolution mechanism fulfils the Organization’s requirements under Section 29 of the Convention to provide an appropriate mode of settlement of disputes arising out of contracts to which the United Nations (in this case UNEP) is a party.\nWe further note that the deviation from standard Dispute Settlement is identical to the one which was made in an earlier SSFA with UGAFT for the same project, and which Legal Unit cleared on an exceptional basis. Given that the current SSFA is for the same project as the one concluded in October 2020, we are accepting this deviation on an exceptional basis for this project ONLY. Kindly note that this exceptional clearance should not be construed to create a precedent for future agreements with UGAFT or with any other implementing partner.',3165,'2021-09-20 11:04:03',NULL,NULL,0),(4469,1524,2777,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Dear Florence, Thank you for your comments.\n1. The amount in words has been added in clause 5.\n2. I am not understanding exactly which standard template text you are referring to - the text including up to Annex E is not present in the standard SSFA template in WeCollaborate. I will reach out via Teams to seek clarifications and ensure a timely resolution to this issue.\nThank you.',2241,'2021-09-20 11:08:23',NULL,NULL,0),(4470,1781,4596,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Dear Florence, Thank you for your comments. For #1, this is revised as requested. For #2, this is revised as requested. For #3, I am not sure I understand your comment and will reach out via Teams for further clarifications. For #4, this is revised as requested. Thank you.',2241,'2021-09-20 11:23:10',NULL,NULL,0),(4471,1364,4554,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','In the last 2 EC verification, the auditor