,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','Please see the below response from Daniel Cooney as Director of the Communication Division: If the Partnership Committee approves this partnership, the next step would be for the Communication Division, together with the Asia-Pacific office (the lead on this proposed partnership), to develop a detailed sponsorship plan with the company for Champions of the Earth. It would detail the brand visibility that the company would get from the sponsorship, and it would make clear that the company would have zero influence in the selection of the Champion laureates. The company and the Chinese government would not be consulted in the entire selection process. Once the proposed sponsorship plan is finalized with the company, the plan would be presented to the ED for approval before any sponsorship agreement is signed.',3197,'2021-10-15 14:40:15',NULL,NULL,0),(4626,2807,4740,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Liesel: Kindly amend the two areas as highlighted in my email.',2507,'2021-10-15 16:17:33',NULL,NULL,0),(4627,3070,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Please upload the latest audited financial statements.',28,'2021-10-18 11:55:42',NULL,NULL,0),(4628,2354,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','Regarding the following comment: as indicated our response to Question 15, they sell tobacco alcohol pursuant to laws and regulations in each jurisdiction. In their Rakuten Shopping Webs, every customer needs to register to use all the services in Rakuten Shopping Webs. If costumers are minors less than 18 years old in Japan, they need to get first approval from their parents and submit its certificate to get approval from Rakuten Inc. before accessing any services. We hope this clarifies this question for the Private Sector Unit. Dear Mabrouk: could you give us your opinions? Best regards, Shunichi Honda. * The Private Sector Unit’s stance is as follows: An excerpt extracted from the UNSDG Common Approach to Prospect Research and Due Diligence for Business Sector Partnerships (https://bit.ly/3AP5aEA) lists Tobacco manufacturers under the Common Set of Exclusionary Criteria section (page 11) and elaborates as follows: \"Entities for whom the core business is the production and wholesale distribution of tobacco products\". This “exclusionary” criterion indicates that production and wholesale distribution of tobacco must be a core business focus. Rakuten is a Japanese electronic commerce and online retailing company. While Rakuten does not manufacture tobacco products, it does sell such products. Tobacco involvement/links triggers a medium risk rating on the Partners Portal (16 DD Questions). This partner has been assessed as a high-risk entity by the Private Sector Unit due to other reputational issues (e.g. labour rights violations) and a risk mitigation plan has been prepared by the partnership lead, Honda Shunichi. The plan should be updated to include that this entity profits from tobacco and how UNEP would mitigate any arising risks pertaining to this aspect. This will allow the Partnership Committee to be in a better position to review this potential partnership. We are also in agreement with Isabel’s view that this potential partnership should be piloted and assessed on an annual basis. The results and impacts of the partnership will dictate whether it should proceed or be discontinued. Ultimately, the Partnership Committee has the final judgement regarding the approval or rejection of this partner. Furthermore, specific information pertaining to this partnership is required. A concise breakdown on what the partnership will exactly entail between UNEP and Rakuten would be very helpful at this stage. The review of this potential partnership should continue and the Private Sector Unit will bilaterally seek more details from the partnership lead. ',2090,'2021-10-18 12:45:48',NULL,NULL,0),(4629,1038,3870,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','1. Is this a bridging agreement ?  If yes, please do it only for the amount of the remaining balance.  \n2. The implementation plan indicates that it is for the year 2021, although the text of the agreement indicates that there are activities to take place in 2022.  Please attach an implementation plan for 2022 with a timeline for the activities indicated.  Budget should also be consistent with implementation plan.  \n3. Please attach the initial SSFA and previous amendments, together with their respective progress and financial reports sent by the IP.   (Quality Assurance)',895,'2021-10-18 17:51:15',NULL,NULL,0),(4630,1905,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'AssesmentQuestions','partners','The statutes (1997) and Constitutive Act (1997) of PADI have been duly recorded. I also note you have submitted a more recent incorporation document from the Haitian authorities (08.2020 - 07.2022). Since these documents have an expiry date, we recommend requesting a new version of the incorporation certificate before the expiration of the current one if the partnership with PADI is to continue beyond July 2022. ',3039,'2021-10-18 19:07:00',NULL,NULL,0),(4631,3072,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'PartnerSummary','partners','Please upload the Certificate of Incorporation/Registration.',28,'2021-10-19 10:12:22',NULL,NULL,0),(4632,450,4724,NULL,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','I have reviewed the legal instrument and note the due diligence expired 11-10-2021.  Grateful if you could have the partner due diligence finalized prior to submitting the agreement. \nFor guidance, kindly see https://wecollaborate.unep.org/display/partners/3.1.1+Modify+Template\nFor technical assistance, kindly reach out to the technical team via  https://wework.unep.org/plugins/servlet/desk/portal/23\nThank you.\n (Quality Assurance)',2112,'2021-10-19 13:41:30',NULL,NULL,0),(4633,2881,4759,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','Dear Nada, for your kind approval on FMO side. Thank you. ',845,'2021-10-19 14:12:12',NULL,NULL,0),(4634,450,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'