draft agreement under 2; activities to be carried out .., with the below text:\nThe main objective of the Institutional Strengthening Project (ISP) is to strengthen the capacity of the EPA, in particular its National Ozone Unit (NOU) to implement the obligations of the Montreal Protocol and its amendments.  \n\nNOU will continue during phase VIII coordination with stakeholders, government & private sectors and updating them on ExCom & MOP decisions and ensure their full engagement in implementing the ongoing MP funded projects including the stage I HPMP and initiate the implementation of stage II to achieve 2025 reduction target as per Montreal Protocol. It will also pursue the implementation of the outcomes of the Kigali Enabling Activities project and continue facilitating the ratification of the Kigali Amendment. The NOU will continue the effective operation of the HCFC quota and licensing system to ensure sustainability of phase out achieved and comply with future reduction targets. it will update the system to include HFCs as required under the Kigali Amendment and will continue efforts to identify feasible alternatives suitable for the HAT countries. NOU will continue producing public and industry awareness materials and programs and preparing MP reports.\n\nDetailed objectives are as detailed in the Terminal Report- Annex 1a.\n (Quality Assurance)',226,'2021-11-03 15:20:32',NULL,NULL,0),(4740,3089,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Comments','partners','Kindly find an update on this partner profile now submitted as an LLC instead of an NGO. I hope the provided information is sufficient to go on with the Due diligence process. \nMany thanks!\nQueen',3286,'2021-11-03 16:26:15',NULL,NULL,0),(4741,3091,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Documents','partners','Please upload relevant validation documents\n ',146,'2021-11-03 21:55:13',NULL,NULL,0),(4742,3083,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Documents','partners',' Please upload relevant validation documents \n',146,'2021-11-03 21:55:52',NULL,NULL,0),(4743,824,4634,0,NULL,2,'AgreementSummary','agreements','please note that while a couple of SSFA/PCAs with University of Geneva with their proposed text under Clause 15a were cleared by the Legal Unit in the past on an exceptional basis and for those specific projects only, there are other SSFAs whereby University of Geneva agreed to include our standard SSFA template’s text under the liability/responsibility provision. Also, please note that not all the SSFAs that you either appended to your e-mail below or are posted in the Portal had been cleared by the Legal Unit. While the Portal is meant to trigger legal review whenever substantive deviations like these are introduced in the agreements, but for some technical errors not all those agreements prompted request for legal review/clearance in the system. \n\nWith reference to the specific text proposed by University of Geneva under Clause 15a of your SSFA, and purely from the legal standpoint, our position and advice remains the same: Regarding the Clause on limited liability, please note that generally we do not accept any limitation on liability, since it may prevent UNEP from being adequately compensated for the contractor\'s failure to perform its obligations. While a limitation clause may be good for the contractor, ultimately the Member States and their taxpaying citizens will bear the cost of such a provision. According to the standard process, UNEP needs to get prior approval of the UN controller on the agreed limitation, before we accept a clause on limited liability.\n\nIn light of the above, we would reiterate our earlier comment and suggest that in lieu of University of Geneva’s proposed text under Clause 15a, you retain the original text from our SSFA template which states: ‘[The Partner] shall be solely and completely responsible and accountable for all services performed by its personnel, agents, employees, or contractors (hereinafter referred to as “Personnel”)’. As we had shared with you earlier, there are a number of SSFAs with University of Geneva where our standard text under the liability/responsibility provision had been accepted by the University. For ease of reference, I am appending herewith a copy of a recent SSFA where our standard clause had been accepted by the University of Geneva (please see Clause 16a of the attached document titled: SSFA_Unige_Including UNEP’s standard liability-responsibility clause). This SSFA was for our Vienna Office, which was concluded by both parties in December 2020.\n\nPlease note that the role of the Legal Unit in Corporate Services Division is to provide advice, and further to such advice, clear -or not- draft agreements. Decisions are to be made by Senior Managers under their responsibility and delegated authority. In line with the Delegation of Authority Policy and Framework, it is within the delegation of authority of the Directors to decide about the signing of agreements, even if they include clauses not cleared by us. It is for them to take the decision on the basis of weighing up the risk and benefit of each specific situation, the probability and impact of the risk .\n',2079,'2021-11-04 06:07:49',NULL,NULL,0);
